<PubmedArticle><MedlineCitation Status="MEDLINE" Owner="NLM" IndexingMethod="Curated"><PMID Version="1">25924643</PMID><DateCompleted><Year>2015</Year><Month>08</Month><Day>06</Day></DateCompleted><DateRevised><Year>2019</Year><Month>12</Month><Day>10</Day></DateRevised><Article PubModel="Print"><Journal><ISSN IssnType="Print">0006-9248</ISSN><JournalIssue CitedMedium="Print"><Volume>116</Volume><Issue>5</Issue><PubDate><Year>2015</Year></PubDate></JournalIssue><Title>Bratislavske lekarske listy</Title><ISOAbbreviation>Bratisl Lek Listy</ISOAbbreviation></Journal><ArticleTitle>The effect of Nesfatin-1 on heart L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channel &#x3b1;1c subunit in rats subjected to chronic restraint stress.</ArticleTitle><Pagination><StartPage>326</StartPage><EndPage>329</EndPage><MedlinePgn>326-9</MedlinePgn></Pagination><Abstract><AbstractText Label="BACKGROUND" NlmCategory="BACKGROUND">Elevated L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a;channel expression level increases Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; influx. This can cause hypertrophy and pathological remodeling of the heart especially under stress conditions. Nesfatin-1 can activate hypothalamic L, P and Q type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channels and increase insulin secretion in pancreatic islet beta cells via activation of L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channels. On the other hand, the effect of nesfatin-1 on cardiac L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channels has not been studied yet.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="OBJECTIVES" NlmCategory="OBJECTIVE">We aimed to identify the effect of peripheral chronic Nesfatin-1 application on cardiac L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channel &#x3b1;1c subunit expression level in normal rats and those subjected to chronic restraint stress.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="METHODS" NlmCategory="METHODS">Three-month aged Wistar albino rats were randomly divided into 4 groups (n = 7) as Control, Stress, Control+Nesfatin-1, and Nesfatin-1+Stress. Rats in groups subjected to restraint stress were placed in a specially built size-manipulable cabin for 2 h/day (between 10:00 and 12:00 a.m.) for 10 consecutive days without allowing water and food intake. Nesfatin-1 segment (0.25 nmol/g bw intraperitoneally) was applied during the 10 consecutive days. Western blot analyses were performed to determine the expression level of L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channel &#x3b1;1c subunit protein in rat cardiac extracts.</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="RESULTS" NlmCategory="RESULTS">Cardiac L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channel &#x3b1;1c subunit protein expression levels were increased significantly after chronic peripheral Nesfatin-1 application in rats subjected to restraint stress (p = 0.032).</AbstractText><AbstractText Label="CONCLUSION" NlmCategory="CONCLUSIONS">We can conclude that Nesfatin-1 can cause cardiac failures during clinical treatments by elevating cardiac L-type Ca&#xb2;&#x207a; channel &#x3b1;1c subunit protein expression level (Fig. 2, Ref. 26).</AbstractText></Abstract><AuthorList CompleteYN="Y"><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Ayada</LastName><ForeName>C</ForeName><Initials>C</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Turgut</LastName><ForeName>G</ForeName><Initials>G</Initials></Author><Author ValidYN="Y"><LastName>Turgut</LastName><ForeName>S</ForeName><Initials>S</Initials></Author></AuthorList><Language>eng</Language><PublicationTypeList><PublicationType UI="D016428">Journal Article</PublicationType><PublicationType UI="D013485">Research Support, Non-U.S. Gov't</PublicationType></PublicationTypeList></Article><MedlineJournalInfo><Country>Germany</Country><MedlineTA>Bratisl Lek Listy</MedlineTA><NlmUniqueID>0065324</NlmUniqueID><ISSNLinking>0006-9248</ISSNLinking></MedlineJournalInfo><ChemicalList><Chemical><RegistryNumber>0</RegistryNumber><NameOfSubstance UI="C504728">Cacna1c protein, rat</NameOfSubstance></Chemical><Chemical><RegistryNumber>0</RegistryNumber><NameOfSubstance UI="D020746">Calcium Channels, L-Type</NameOfSubstance></Chemical><Chemical><RegistryNumber>0</RegistryNumber><NameOfSubstan